{"key":"post-10782351","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10782351</id>\n<content>Two 1/4&quot; holes is going to allow a bit much exchange and could lead to drying of the grains and premature pinning.&amp;nbsp; I'd stick to four 1/8&quot; holes.&amp;nbsp; Just get a drill bit set at any hardware store, and always have a piece of wood behind the metal as you drill.&amp;nbsp; If you buy jars by the case, you can drill all twelve lids in one shot by stacking them.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10782459</next>\n<prev>10782255</prev>\n<first>10781404</first>\n<last>10782459</last>\n<when>1249180473</when>\n<utime>08/02/09 05:34 AM</utime>\n</post>"}